  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "The gulper eel attacks. Near-zero attack (1ms), fast decay (0.3s), no sustain — a percussive sub hit. Wreck body mode with high feedback creates a metallic snap on the transient. Pressure at 0.9 squashes the peak into a physical thump. The bio exciter adds a bright flash at 3500 Hz on each strike — the bioluminescent burst of a predator lunging. Designed for 808-adjacent sub drops.",
  "tags": [
    "bass",
    "percussive",
    "hit",
    "sub-drop",
    "808",
    "guru-bin",
    "transcendental"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OCEANDEEP — Transcendental Vol 1",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "scripture": ["Verse: Pressure Is the Synthesis", "Canon 1: The Tape Ceiling — Saturation at 0.03-0.08"],
    "revelation": "Pressura spoke: ampAtk at 0.001 with pressureAmt at 0.9 creates an inverted dynamic — the louder the initial transient, the harder it gets compressed. The result is a thump that hits chest then immediately retreats. The gulper's jaw unhinges and snaps shut in 300 milliseconds.",
    "god": "Pressura",
    "flock_note": "The Tongue found that this preset responds to velocity like a drum machine: vel 40 = gentle tap, vel 100 = solid hit, vel 127 = the room shakes. The Bone confirmed: at 3% CPU this is the cheapest 808-class sound in the fleet.",
    "diagnosis": "This sound was a sustained bass pretending to be percussive. It is now a deep-sea predator strike — pure transient energy shaped by the hydrostatic compressor into physical impact."
  },
